# Arcane Cloud (M1C) — copy to .env to configure. M1C needs a real Postgres (Supabase): the sync
# cursor stays in-memory + the shadow worktree on disk, but RESULTS (scores/findings) persist to
# Postgres. Fill DATABASE_URL/DIRECT_URL from your Supabase project (Settings → Database).
# The .env file is git-ignored.

# WS/REST port the gateway listens on.
PORT=8787

# Pooled connection (port 6543) — used by the running server (db/client.ts). REQUIRED in M1C.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@<host>:6543/postgres

# Direct connection (port 5432) — used by `bun run migrate` (DDL needs the direct connection).
DIRECT_URL=postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@<host>:5432/postgres

# STUB dev token (Build Guide §18) — the single token that gates /auth/token, /link, and /ingest.
# `arcane login` fetches this from /auth/token; real OAuth device login (§23) is a later milestone.
ARCANE_DEV_TOKEN=dev-stub-token

# Optional: where per-project shadow worktrees are materialized (defaults to ./.arcane-shadow).
# ARCANE_SHADOW_ROOT=/tmp/arcane-shadow

# M1D — Supabase Realtime fan-out. The running SERVER needs NOTHING here: it writes result_events via
# DATABASE_URL (postgres role, bypasses RLS), and the browser reads them live via Realtime. These two
# are ONLY for the headless realtime PROOF (src/__tests__/realtime.test.ts), which subscribes as an
# ANON client to exercise the publication + RLS. service_role never goes here, in the proof, or the
# browser — anon only (RLS-enforced, public-safe).
# SUPABASE_URL=https://<ref>.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon / publishable key — Supabase → Settings → API; NOT service_role>

# GitHub App connector (Technical-Spec §13) — a SECOND analysis source: a push to a connected repo is
# fetched and analyzed server-side, fanning findings to the dashboard exactly like the CLI path. All
# three come from the GitHub App you create at github.com/settings/apps (Contents+Metadata: Read-only,
# subscribe to Push events). Server-side only — the thin CLI never sees these. Leave unset to disable.
# GITHUB_APP_ID=<numeric App ID — App settings → "App ID">
# GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<the webhook secret you set on the App — verifies X-Hub-Signature-256>
# GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY=<the .pem contents; keep the BEGIN/END lines, newlines as \n if single-line>
